# Roadmap / Backlog — keep CHANGELOG and docs/roadmap in sync

When **adding, editing, removing, re-versioning**, or marking backlog items done in
**`CHANGELOG.md`** (section `### Roadmap / Backlog`), **always update** the interactive
page under `docs/roadmap/`.

## Files and roles

| File | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | Source of truth (Keep a Changelog); release notes |
| `docs/roadmap/roadmap-data.js` | UI data (`window.NSSM_ROADMAP`: versions, tracks, tasks, validate, checklist) |
| `docs/roadmap/index.html` | Shell — edit only when changing layout/UI features |
| `docs/roadmap/roadmap.css` / `roadmap-app.js` | Style & behavior — only when changing UX |

## Checklist when changing the backlog

1. Edit **`CHANGELOG.md`** (description, Validate, new version).
2. Mirror in **`roadmap-data.js`**: stable task `id` (e.g. `226-b1`), `title`, `detail`, `validate`, `depends`, `theme`.
3. New version → add object in `versions[]`, update `meta.chain`, `releaseChecklist` if needed.
4. Delete/rename task → update or remove matching entry (orphaned localStorage ticks are acceptable).
5. Open `docs/roadmap/index.html` — verify timeline, search, progress.

## `roadmap-data.js` conventions

- **`theme`:** `build` | `ci` | `compat` | `service` | `quality` | `docs`
- Each task: `id`, `title`, `detail`, `validate`; `highlight: true` if notable; `tag: "refactor"` for refactors.
- Shipped item → **Added** in the matching CHANGELOG version; remove from backlog or move to `released.highlights`.

## Shipped releases

- On a new release: update `shippedReleases` (newest first), `released`, `meta.currentRelease`.
- Create `docs/release/<x.y.z>/` (data `window.NSSM_RELEASE_<XYZ>`) for HTML release notes; set `releaseNotes`. If none → `releaseNotes: null` (CHANGELOG link only).

## Not required to sync

- Detailed shipped release prose (old Added/Changed sections) — update `released` only when bumping the current version.
- Upstream history (NSSM ≤ 2.24) — static; no roadmap mirror.
